00:05:15.410 --> 00:05:16.850
move into delivery.

00:05:16.850 --> 00:05:19.710
Also, engineering teams are
more happy at this point

00:05:19.710 --> 00:05:22.130
because their probability
of what they are building

00:05:22.130 --> 00:05:26.090
in the delivery track is higher
because we already validated

00:05:26.090 --> 00:05:29.070
key hypotheses in discovery.

00:05:29.070 --> 00:05:31.490
So to give you an
idea and trying

00:05:31.490 --> 00:05:35.090
to also jump into a
real life example of how

00:05:35.090 --> 00:05:38.970
we had to leverage qualitative
data in combination

00:05:38.970 --> 00:05:42.410
with quantitative ones, look
at this very simple step

00:05:42.410 --> 00:05:44.340
in our old onboarding.

00:05:44.340 --> 00:05:45.660
So again, we teach English.

00:05:45.660 --> 00:05:49.040
So in the onboarding
stage, we were asking users

00:05:49.040 --> 00:05:54.290
to tell us what was their
initial level of English.

00:05:54.290 --> 00:05:57.230
If we look at only
quantitative data,

00:05:57.230 --> 00:05:59.590
we weren't losing so
many users in this step.

00:05:59.590 --> 00:06:03.710
Actually, barely nobody was
dropping off at this point.

00:06:03.710 --> 00:06:06.920
Every user was
selecting a level.

00:06:06.920 --> 00:06:08.390
But you know what?

00:06:08.390 --> 00:06:12.230
When we started in analyzing
their sentiment in this stage,

00:06:12.230 --> 00:06:15.770
we discovered that many users
were actually frustrated.

00:06:15.770 --> 00:06:18.440
How do I assess my
level of English?

00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:21.530
And how this is going to
work out at the end for me

00:06:21.530 --> 00:06:22.280
in the app?

00:06:22.280 --> 00:06:25.280
What we found out
is that, eventually,

00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:27.110
the fact that
users were randomly

00:06:27.110 --> 00:06:30.680
selecting level of
English in this stage

00:06:30.680 --> 00:06:33.530
led to abandonment later on.

00:06:33.530 --> 00:06:35.960
We had users that were
overestimating their level.

00:06:35.960 --> 00:06:39.920
And they were basically facing
with too difficult exercises,

00:06:39.920 --> 00:06:43.400
and vice versa, users were
underestimating themselves

00:06:43.400 --> 00:06:45.500
and finding the
exercises we were

00:06:45.500 --> 00:06:47.960
proposing too easy for them.

00:06:47.960 --> 00:06:50.210
So we worked in a solution.

00:06:50.210 --> 00:06:52.010
We prototyped
different solutions

00:06:52.010 --> 00:06:53.770
to try to address this issue.

00:06:53.770 --> 00:06:55.400
And at the end we
went for one that

00:06:55.400 --> 00:06:57.650
was kind of counterintuitive.

00:06:57.650 --> 00:07:01.280
We created a way longer
funnel during the onboarding.

00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:04.310
Now we ask users to
take a level test.

00:07:04.310 --> 00:07:07.285
Yes, we still have easy path.

00:07:07.285 --> 00:07:09.660
If you're a beginner, if you
want to skip the onboarding,

00:07:09.660 --> 00:07:11.460
then you can still do that.

00:07:11.460 --> 00:07:15.290
But our new happy path for
users onboarding the app

00:07:15.290 --> 00:07:17.118
goes through a level test.

00:07:17.118 --> 00:07:18.910
And again, it's
counterintuitive because we

00:07:18.910 --> 00:07:22.210
were adding many steps in
the onboarding process.

00:07:22.210 --> 00:07:24.370
You will think, OK,
many more steps,

00:07:24.370 --> 00:07:26.320
the funnel will be longer.

00:07:26.320 --> 00:07:27.610
And you will lose users.

00:07:27.610 --> 00:07:30.650
Well, it wasn't that the case.

00:07:30.650 --> 00:07:33.460
In fact, what we saw
overall, with these

00:07:33.460 --> 00:07:36.160
and all other experiments
that we did on the onboarding,

00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:40.150
is that we achieved double
activation in our app.

00:07:40.150 --> 00:07:43.400
And again, if we were only to
focus on the quantitative data,

00:07:43.400 --> 00:07:47.380
we were never going to discover
where the real problem was.

00:07:47.380 --> 00:07:51.070
So again, what we
learn, as a company,

00:07:51.070 --> 00:07:53.680
is that you need to
go to the source.

00:07:53.680 --> 00:07:55.600
You need to talk
with your customers,

00:07:55.600 --> 00:07:58.330
eventually even going
out of the building.

00:07:58.330 --> 00:08:03.020
Complement quantitative
data with qualitative data.

00:08:03.020 --> 00:08:05.650
Bring it into your
full development cycle.

00:08:05.650 --> 00:08:08.800
Make it practice for you
to have this feedback

00:08:08.800 --> 00:08:11.020
into your development cycle.

00:08:11.020 --> 00:08:12.560
And ultimately, experiment.

00:08:12.560 --> 00:08:14.140
Experiment a lot
because, at the end,

00:08:14.140 --> 00:08:16.270
it's what really is
going to help you

00:08:16.270 --> 00:08:19.370
find the successful solutions.

